x4freetext: Absolute reaction cross sections were determined by
comparison of the (d,p) and (d,t) intensities with the
yield of elastically scattered deuterons.
Two different methods have been used to fabricate 204Hg
targets. In the first method macromolecular
electrospraying was used. The target was finally
covered with a thin foil of formvar to reduce the
evaporation of the target material. The target had a
mercury thickness of about 340 mu-g/cm2. The mercuro
nitrate solution used for the preparation of the
sprayed targets had the following isotopic composition:
In the second method the Aarhus mass separator was used
The targets had a mercury thickness of about 50mu-g/cm2
deposited in a layer of 2Al3O about 125 mu-g/cm2 thick.
The isotopic composition was 100% 204Hg.
In the NBI experiments, the reaction
products were analyzed at 90 and 125 degr. in a single-
gap, magnetic spectrograph, with photographic detection
The experimental cross sections have a relative
uncertainty of +-10%. The absolute scale has an
uncertainty of +-30%.
Tbl.1 p. 21
